<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-10-30T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-10-30T14:00:00-05:00" n="583" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d583">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">707.1161/17: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Sheffield</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico
                                        City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-10-30T12:00:00-07:00"><hi rend="italic">October 30,
                                        1924—noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received 4:25
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>396. Department’s circular of August 27, 1 p.m.<note n="4" xml:id="d583fn4">See footnote 1, <ref target="#pg_676">p.
                                676</ref>.</note> In my capacity as dean of the diplomatic corps it
                            may be necessary for me to present the chiefs of missions to the new
                            President of the Republic on December 1st.</p>
                        <p>Please advise what action I should take in regard to presentation of the
                            new Soviet Minister shortly to arrive here.</p>
                        <p>Please advise what action I should take [in] his case should it be
                            necessary at any future time for me as dean to call a meeting of the
                            diplomatic corps.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Sheffield</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>